Quiñonero-Coronel et al., Microbial Genomics 2025;11:001409 DOI 10.1099/mgen.0.001409
Received 03 January 2025; Accepted 01 April 2025; Published 23 May 2025 Author affiliations: 1Instituto de Biomedicina y Biotecnología de Cantabria (IBBTEC), Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Científicas-Universidad de Cantabria, Santander, Spain; 2School of Life Sciences, University of Warwick, Coventry, UK; 3Evolutionary Genomics Group, Departamento Producción Vegetal y Microbiología, Universidad Miguel Hernández, Alicante, Spain. *Correspondence: M. Pilar Garcillán-Barcia, maria.garcillan@csic.es; garcilmp@unican.es Keywords: Patescibacteria; Candidate Phyla Radiation; horizontal gene transfer; type IV secretion system. Abbreviations: CPR, Candidate Phyla Radiation; GTDB, Genome Taxonomy Database; HMM, Hidden Markov model; ICEs, integrative and conjugative elements; MPF, mating pair formation; SH-aLRT, SH-like approximate likelihood ratio test; T4SS, type IV secretion system; UFBoot, ultrafast bootstrap. 001409 © 2025 The Authors
